## Data & Results

A structured dataset was collected to evaluate the functional performance of the tendon-driven prosthetic system under repeated trials. Testing focused on quantifying grasp success, precision capability, and repeatability.

---

### Data Collection Methodology

- Tests were conducted under consistent conditions using manual tendon actuation  
- Standardised objects were used for repeatability (cylindrical and small precision objects)  
- Each test consisted of 20 independent trials to capture variability  
- Outcomes were recorded as binary results (Success / Failure)  
- Repeatability was assessed across consecutive grasp cycles  

